        <publication-year>1869</publication-year>
        <review>&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 20px; font-family: sans-serif; "/&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;War and Peace&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#160;(&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_language" title="Russian language" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Russian&lt;/a&gt;:&#160;&lt;span lang="ru"&gt;Война и мир&lt;/span&gt;,&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_the_Russian_language" title="History of the Russian language" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Pre-reform Russian&lt;/a&gt;: «Война и миръ») is a&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Novel" title="Novel" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;novel&lt;/a&gt;&#160;by the&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia" title="Russia" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Russian&lt;/a&gt;&#160;author&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leo_Tolstoy" title="Leo Tolstoy" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Leo Tolstoy&lt;/a&gt;, published in 1869. The work is&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epic_poetry" title="Epic poetry" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;epic&lt;/a&gt;&#160;in scale and is considered one of the most celebrated works of&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fiction" title="Fiction" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;fiction&lt;/a&gt;.&#160;It is regarded as Tolstoy's finest literary achievement, along with his other famous work&#160;&lt;i&gt;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anna_Karenina" title="Anna Karenina" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Anna Karenina&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#160;(1873–1877).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;&lt;i&gt;War and Peace&lt;/i&gt;&#160;delineates in graphic detail events leading up to&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="mw-redirect" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Napoleon" title="Napoleon" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Napoleon&lt;/a&gt;'s&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/French_invasion_of_Russia" title="French invasion of Russia" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;invasion of Russia&lt;/a&gt;, and the impact of the&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Napoleonic_era" title="Napoleonic era" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Napoleonic era&lt;/a&gt;&#160;on&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="mw-redirect" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tsarist" title="Tsarist" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Tsarist&lt;/a&gt;&#160;society, as seen through the eyes of five&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia" title="Russia" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Russian&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aristocracy" title="Aristocracy" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;aristocratic&lt;/a&gt;&#160;families. Portions of an earlier version were serialized in the magazine&#160;&lt;i&gt;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Russian_Messenger" title="The Russian Messenger" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;The Russian Messenger&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#160;between 1865 and 1867. The novel was first published in its entirety in 1869.&#160;&lt;i&gt;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Newsweek" title="Newsweek" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Newsweek&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#160;in 2009 ranked it top of its list of&#160;&lt;i&gt;Top 100 Books&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;Tolstoy himself, somewhat enigmatically, said of&#160;&lt;i&gt;War and Peace&lt;/i&gt;&#160;that it was "not a novel, even less is it a poem, and still less an historical chronicle."&lt;br clear="none"/&gt;&lt;br clear="none"/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 11px; line-height: 15px; "&gt;Text is available under the&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" rel="license" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Text_of_Creative_Commons_Attribution-ShareAlike_3.0_Unported_License" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike License&lt;/a&gt;; additional terms may apply. See&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" href="http://wikimediafoundation.org/wiki/Terms_of_Use" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Terms of Use&lt;/a&gt;&#160;for details.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br clear="none"/&gt;</review>
